commentary: Dissolved the concept of 'Software' and placed under 'System' which now includes hardward, software, and the collection of both. Added InstanceOf to System which both ties together physical and logical systems into the same model, allows for OOP style inheritance, and permits for duplicate systems in the same model. Vulnerabilities and Risks had first major overhaul since inception of Cyber Data Schema that now ties together Susceptibilities and permits for shareable Vulnerabilities and Risks in a enterprise wide context.

tables.name: MissionData
tables.description: Defined as the operational data associated with unique missions and the attributes pertaining to the specific relationship. Operational data can either be an input for or generated by Missions. Additionally, for input data, Operational Data can be flagged as either MissionCritical or not. For example, if your mission is to drive to a store you've never been to, then GPS data could be considered mission critical however your music playlist would be a non mission critical input. Whereas for the mission 'Impressing your date' your music playlist would be deemed mission critical.

tables.description: Process or policy governing how information is distributed or transmitted among authorized recipients. tables.name: ClassificationControlCaveats
tables.description: specific markers or notations applied to classified information that impose additional handling restrictions beyond the basic classification level. These caveats are used to limit access to information within a specific group of users or for a particular purpose. For example, a control caveat might specify that certain information can only be accessed by individuals involved in a specific operation or mission, regardless of their general security clearance level. Common caveats include NOFORN, REL TO, etc.
